# Code Style

## CSS
- Use existing CSS variables only — never hardcode colors or radii
  - Colors: `var(--bg)`, `var(--ink)`, `var(--salmon)`, `var(--border)`, etc.
  - Radii: `var(--radius)` (8px), `var(--radius-lg)` (16px)
- Dark mode is handled via `[data-theme="dark"]` overrides — never use `prefers-color-scheme`
- All transitions on theme-affected properties must use `0.3s ease`
- Never add inline styles to HTML unless absolutely unavoidable. Use classes.
- New component classes go at the bottom of the relevant CSS file with a `/* ── LABEL ── */` header comment

## HTML
- Use semantic tags (`<section>`, `<aside>`, `<nav>`, `<footer>`, `<main>`)
- All images must have `alt` attributes
- Buttons that are not form submits must have `type="button"`
- No inline `onclick` handlers — use `addEventListener` in JS

## JavaScript
- All JS is vanilla, no frameworks or imports
- Wrap all logic in `(function () { 'use strict'; })()` IIFEs
- Use `const` and `let`, never `var`
- Event listeners go in the relevant JS file, never inline in HTML

## Fonts
- Headings and UI: `'Epilogue', sans-serif`
- Monospace/labels/code: `'JetBrains Mono', monospace`
- Never introduce new font families

## Naming
- CSS classes use kebab-case
- JS variables use camelCase
- IDs use kebab-case